"title": "1325: God, the Creator",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1325",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's power is revealed in the initial creation and the continuing sustenance of the universe. Humanity represents the climax of the Creator's purposes.</p>\n<h2>God is the Creator</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:6\">NEH 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1\">GEN 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:7\">ISA 45:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2\">ISA 66:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:9\">EPH 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:11\">REV 4:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's creative activity demonstrates his uniqueness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:5\">PSA 96:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:16\">ISA 37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:11\">JER 10:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's creative activity implies that he is good</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:4\">1TI 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:4\">GEN 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:31\">GEN 1:31</a></p>\n<h2>God creates all things</h2>\n<h3>He creates the physical world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:18\">ISA 45:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1-Gen1:25\">GEN 1:1–1:25</a></p>\n<h3>He creates the spiritual world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:2-Ps148:5\">PSA 148:2–148:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>The human race is the apex of God's creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:3-Ps8:8\">PSA 8:3–8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:28\">GEN 1:26–1:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:1\">GEN 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">GEN 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:3\">PSA 100:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:13\">PSA 139:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:5\">ISA 42:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:26-Acts17:28\">ACT 17:26–17:28</a></p>\n<h2>The Creator's agents</h2>\n<h3>He creates through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:3\">JHN 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>He creates by the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:4\">JOB 33:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:2\">GEN 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:30\">PSA 104:30</a></p>\n<h3>He creates by his word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:8-Job38:11\">JOB 38:8–38:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:9\">PSA 33:9</a></p>\n<h3>He creates by wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:19\">PRO 3:19</a></strong> <em>Wisdom is personified and is active with the Creator.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:30\">PRO 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:12-Jer10:13\">JER 10:12–10:13</a></p>\n<h2>He creates from nothing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:3\">HEB 11:3</a></strong> <em>God creates out of non-existent material, which emphasises the absolute dependence of all creation upon him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:7\">JOB 26:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:17\">ROM 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>The Creator sustains the created order</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24\">ISA 44:24</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew indicates continuous activity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:20\">DEU 30:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:8-Job9:9\">JOB 9:8–9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:2-Ps104:4\">PSA 104:2–104:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:5\">ISA 42:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of God sustaining creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:45\">MAT 5:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:10\">JOB 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:31-Job38:33\">JOB 38:31–38:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:28-Matt6:30\">MAT 6:28–6:30</a></p>\n<h2>The Creator watches over his creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:14\">PSA 33:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:2-Ps121:8\">PSA 121:2–121:8</a></p>\n<h2>The creation is a vehicle for God's self-revelation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:20\">ROM 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:1\">PSA 19:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:26\">ISA 40:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:13\">AMO 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>God renews his creation through redemption</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:17\">JHN 3:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:17\">ROM 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4\">ROM 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:23\">ROM 8:19–8:23</a> <em>The redemption of the physical world must wait until the sons of God are revealed at the end of time</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:15\">GAL 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>God renews his new creation of believing people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:16\">2CO 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:10\">COL 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>God will reveal a new universe</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:5\">REV 21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17\">ISA 65:17</a></p>",
